Title: Lupine Observations
Description: Defeat Fangsnap in Fangsnap's Den for Survivalist Wilson in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Animals talking, walking on two legs, and at least one of them is even taking on human form.\n\nMy theory is that Angry Earth's infected them with lycanthropy - we have ourselves a legitimate werewolf!
InProgressResponse: If my suspicions are correct and animals really are taking on human form, things are gonna change.\n\nWe humans might soon go from being predators to being prey.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You did it then? You hunted down the monstrous beast, Fangsnap? \n\nI'm guessing he didn't take on his human form, but I swear it's true. I've seen the tracks. Either way, the damn thing needed to be destroyed.

Title: Pirates Will Pirate
Description: Defeat Neptunite Pirates and collect Pirate Booty from chests for Constable Muller in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Rilette Wilson's claiming there's a werewolf stalking the shore, and others say the Lost have gone to war.\n\nThe soulless, aimless Lost fighting each other - it makes no sense. I don't buy it.
InProgressResponse: I mean, how long have the Lost pirates of Aeternum been raiding the supplies of the living?\n\nIt's normal Lost pirate behavior, nothing more.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Haha! You gave those damn buccaneers a little payback, didn't you? Let's see the spoils!\n\nPerfect! This should make everyone happy, get things back to normal. Thank you, {playerName}.

Title: War of the Lost
Description: Defeat Seele's Withered at the Decayed Campsite for Magistrate Gurkin in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Indeed. The Lost Buccaneers have been fighting the Withered and vice versa.\n\nTo see the Lost with such focus and intention is disturbing, and the worst part is that Constable Muller won't even acknowledge it!
InProgressResponse: I tell you - I've fought them myself - I've seen the look in their eyes and the way it's changed.\n\nThe Lost are finding some sense of purpose, and we need to prevent that.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've seen for yourself now, haven't you? They fight with increased ferocity, with more precision, with purpose.\n\nStriking a blow to the Withered was the perfect thing. Thank you.

Title: The Greater Threat
Description: Kill Eastshore Forces at the Eastshore Pier and Gather Fishing Supplies for Magistrate Gurkin in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes! You get it, right? It sounds harmless in a way, but it's further evidence that they are more and more sentient.\n\nI swear by the Ancients, this is the most terrifying thing I have heard yet.
InProgressResponse: There was a time I used to fish from the Eastshore Pier myself.\n\nThat was back before it fell to the Lost in the first place.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hah! No more fishing for the Lost! That should stop them from getting ideas.\n\nI just hope it's enough. Artificer Taethen and I are still trying to get Constable Muller to come around.

Title: Disarmament (Elite)
Description: Confiscate grenades from chests and destroy Ching Shih the Shark for Artificer Taethen in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Those blasted Lost Buccaneers are arming themselves, even developing new weapons.\n\nIt's unheard of for the Lost, and we need to disarm the soulless bastards before it catches on.
InProgressResponse: Watch yourself out there. Rumor says the pirates' grenades are enhanced with azoth.\n\nNever thought I'd see the day.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Took down Ching Shih the shark, did you? And you got the grenades? Well done, {playerName}.\n\nThat'll cut a hole in their sails, I tell you. Let's hope the Lost Pirate forget all about their ambitions.

Title: Slaying the Shadowslayer
Description: Kill Erika the Shadowslayer in Solitude Cemetery for Artificer Taethen in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Exactly. With the Pirates pushed back, the Withered are now on the offensive.\n\nIt's their leader we need to deal with - the Shadowslayer - she's been a dark threat here for decades, and even darker now.
InProgressResponse: Destroy the Shadowslayer, {playerName}, whatever it takes.\n\nThen go and try to convince the Constable to finally acknowledge our plight.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So you went out and dealt with the Shadowslayer? It's about time someone did that.\n\nI know you've been working with Gurkin too, but come on, you aren't buying into this idea of the Lost being more advanced, are you?

Title: Where The Boars Roam
Description: Defeat Boars and Tuskgore at Boarsholm for Survivalist Wilson in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I am quite certain that the boar in question is responsible for slaying a traveler to the north. \n\nEven more concerning - I've come to believe that this lycanthropy is contagious, too.
InProgressResponse: If we let this strange new mutation from the Angry Earth spread, our days our numbered.\n\nDestroy Tuskgore, for the safety and security of everyone on Aeternum.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The deed's done then? Tuskgore is no more? That is a big relief.\n\nThat boar was a monster and if my theory about Lycanthropy is true, the danger was even greater still.

Title: Scouting Report
Description: Destroy Channelview Pirates in Channelview Post and Oceanview Pirates in Oceanview Post and look for anything suspicious. Then report back to Constable Muller in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That's the fort up on the hill. Once upon a time, that's where the region was governed from.\n\nA naval force from the Arabian Sea reigned supreme - then they all became Lost.
InProgressResponse: The more I think about this, the more I start to worry.\n\nMaybe I should've listened to Gurkin from the start.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank the stars you're back! What did you find? Runestones... what the heck?\n\nMaybe it's some kind of Ancient magic that's giving the bastards this renewed sense of purpose?

Title: Damnation's Fall
Description: Defeat Admiral Reis in the center ship of Fort Damnation. Then report back to Constable Muller in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Launch a frontal attack on Fort Damnation? Are you out of your mind? \n\nWait, don't answer that. Here's the thing, it's not the fort itself that's the problem, it's the fort's commander, Admiral Reis.
InProgressResponse: I'll give you this much - you've already proven to have the strength to back up your bravado - but if you're going to take on Admiral Reis, you'd best be prepared.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well, I thought I'd see the sun rise in the west before I saw anyone take down Admiral Reis.\n\nI gotta hand it to you - you are a force to be reckoned with. I think it only fitting you receive a proper reward.

Title: Paying Respects
Description: Travel to Mourningdale and convey Barkeep Andris's respects to Barkeep Brewell.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Watcher there, Guerra - he fell to the Lost. Quite  a hero, I understand.\n\nIn fact, if you pass through Mourningdale, please offer my condolences to Barkeep Brewell. We go back a ways.
InProgressResponse: The news from Mourningdale is tragic, indeed.\n\nIt almost make me feel guilty that things are going so well here.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Come and sit down and have a drink on the house, traveler.\n\nWe all mourn the passing of a hero today - Watcher Guerra - did you know of him?

Title: Archdeacon Azamela (Expedition)
Description: Collect the head of Archdeacon Azamela in The Depths for Magistrate Gurkin.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You’re damn right, there is! The Corrupted! The Shattered Mountain? \n\nJust when we thought we'd earned a reprieve, now the Corrupted have a foothold, right here in Restless Shore.
InProgressResponse: Who knows what darkness this Archdeacon Azamela is cooking up in the Depths.\n\nAs you said, they must be driven out of Restless Shore, and kept out.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is that it? You destroyed the Archdeacon, didn't you? There's another blow for righteousness and the good of humanity!\n\nWell done, {playerName}, and as promised, here is your reward.

Title: Hoppy Trails
Description: Visit Rabbit Island and if you can find any signs of a curse then deal with them and then return to Survivalist Wilson in the Restless Shores Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: This request is a bit more... unconventional. There is a small island nearby I would like you to investigate. \n\nRabbit Island is a great source of meat and fur but recently the hunters of the settlement have been avoiding it, claiming it to be cursed.
InProgressResponse: A man used to live on that island all by his lonesome, kept to himself and his rabbits well enough. Perhaps you could ask him about the rumors of a haunting of the island and see what he makes of all of this?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So the Harekeeper passed on? I'm glad you put him to rest. His furry friends will flourish with or without him, I suspect. \n\nBut I imagine they'll miss their kindly caretaker. Maybe I'll miss the Harekeep a little myself, as well.

Title: The First Thing I Remember
Description: Discover Santiago Salazar's past by confronting members of his former crew and tracking down a ship manifest and their journal entries.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have flashes of a ship voyage, but that doesn’t say much. Who here hasn't arrived by boat? But there's more... \n\nThe answers I need lie on that island across the channel. Without answers, I fear I may slip away…
InProgressResponse: I appreciate your help. I'd forget my own head if it wasn’t attached. \n\nWhat was I was looking for? My name on a manifest, right?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You're back! I feared you’d end up a soulless Withered, wandering the beaches like old Captain Cross. \n\nBut you seem troubled. What did you discover?

Title: Footsteps on the Beach
Description: Retrace Santiago Salazars steps to find what he placed in a chest and recover Rosario's Manifest from one of his previous crewmembers.
PlayerPrompt: "I suppose it's understandable given your condition."
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
You’re too kind. But I’m certain the answer lies on these shores. 

At the bar in the settlement, I heard from Niki Andris that I sailed on the Rosario. That feels right. 

Now I recall I lost something precious there.
InProgressResponse: When I think of all my precious keepsakes scattered on these shores, I wonder what more I’m missing? \n\nWere they earrings? A bracelet? I'm eager to see what you find.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You’ve returned! And look at that! You found my missing jewelry! That ring! That brooch! And how could I forget that solid gold locket!

Title: The True Terror of the Seas
Description: Confront Santiago Salazar's previous captain Scurvyhook, and extract revenge to put Santiago's mind at ease.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: He now goes by Scurvyhook. Never was there a captain more cruel! \n\nManaged to kill a crew member every day we were at sea. Not to mention taking all our fine cargo for himself!
InProgressResponse: I finally understand why I tried so hard to forget my past. \n\nHelp me lay my personal demons to rest by taking on Scurvyhook. His reign of terror must end!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is the deed done? Have you destroyed those bilge rats and their vile captain? Has Scurvyhook been sent to the abyss?

Title: A Pirate's Life
Description: Follow a trail of Doubloons to reclaim the treasure Santiago's old crew had stashed away years ago.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh, right. We were merchants. But we took what we were owed! The crew hid Scurvyhook’s prized golden stash as payment for our suffering. \n\nIf you find it, I can guarantee a cut. We’ll split it three ways, Niki, you, and me.
InProgressResponse: There's more to life than mourning what was lost. \n\nThat treasure should help set me on a new path, making up for years of wandering this blasted beach.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You look like you need a drink. Hoodwinked by Salazar, were you? You weren't the first, and won't be the last. \n\nDid he give you the whole 'woe is me, I'm becoming Lost' tale?

Title: Broken Communication
Description: Recover Myrtilus's Bow from the Angry Earth at Pisces.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Aside from one who is blind to the land talking with us? The seasons are amiss in Verdant Ascent. \n\nThis is not widely known, but we have lost contact with our brethren in Edengrove. It is troubling.
InProgressResponse: Our bow was left where the fish swim across the sky. \n\nIt is likely one of our siblings picked it up, if only to prevent us from leaving so easily. They were against us sprouting out on our own. Please return our bow.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Impressive! We did not expect much. All you did at first was stare. \n\nOh, you’re still staring. Are you not aware that different petals may grow from the same plant? So too do different plants serve different purposes.

Title: Spined Ammunition
Description: Recover Myrtilus's Quiver and Thornpoint Arrows from the Angry Earth at Fornax.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: If we returned, it would be like an early winter frost. There would be long discourses about the merits of staying secure at Eridanus. \n\nWhich would be as good as never leaving at all. We cannot sit by and allow that.
InProgressResponse: The Thornpoint arrows were made specifically for use with this bow. Like a layer of strong bark, they protect against all sorts of dangers on the road. \n\nWe cannot leave without our arrows.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Once again you do not disappoint. These arrows shall do nicely. \n\nNow we are adequately protected against any dangers that would endeavor to stop us along the road. If only all humans were this helpful.

Title: Trail Rations
Description: Recover Nutrient Stalks from containers at Eridanus for Myrtilus.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: When times are good, a pleasant rain and warm sunlight is enough. \n\nBut in times of high stress, and indeed when we sustain heavy damage, we require more than what the earth can provide to set things right and speed our healing.
InProgressResponse: It is best to rely on sustenance untouched by foulness. \n\nPlease bring us the nourishment we need to begin our journey.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: We can smell the freshness of the nutrient stalks from here. We relish the chance to have a taste while on the road. \n\nThere is nothing quite like the taste of home to restore all balance and mend all ills.

Title: Unnatural Habitation
Description: Search Clawpoint Ruins for any clues as to why there are lynx in the area.
PlayerPrompt: "It's not like we can just leave."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: True. We're trapped on this island. Just like those poor lynx. \n\nYou know, someone brought those animals into Restless Shore. They aren’t native to this part of the island.
InProgressResponse: The clues are out there, I know it. \n\nI can feel the answer is at Clawpoint Ruins. Search the ruins and let me know what you discover.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Let me guess – you found cages, didn’t you?

Title: A Hair's Breadth from Danger
Description: Search the poacher's camp for any letters about their activities.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: When I visited the poachers camp, I was able to get answers to some of my questions, but it was clear there was more to their plans. \n\nI didn't find all their notes. I'm sure there is more information hidden around their camp.
InProgressResponse: I need more information about what those poachers were doing.  The lynx were just the smallest part of their plan. \n\nI'll stay here and keep watch on the ruins, in case those poachers track me down.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Something has changed. Don’t tell me they've returned! \n\nBlast it, I should have burned that place to the ground when I had the chance!

Title: Rule of Tooth and Claw
Description: Right the wrongs done to the local wolf pack.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Our choices are limited. The damage has been done. And we don't have anything that can counter what they did. \n\nIt's a hard choice, but I think the only humane thing is to put the wolves down.
InProgressResponse: You go on ahead, I'll be right behind you. \n\nThe wolf cave isn't that far away, you can't miss it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
So, you met the mad Caryn Berzs. She’s an odd one, I’ll give you that. 

She’s wanted for freeing the local dogs. Said we were monsters for locking them up. 

I bet she expects us to pay you for your work.

Title: Fisherman's Allure
Description: Search for treasure at Poseidon's Plunder for Wafa Keles.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: What do I have to offer? I’m good at spearfishing. And few can climb sea-slick rocks as well as I can. \n\nBut I'm not rich. I have nothing that would interest Xue.
InProgressResponse: I don't have much, but what I do have I'm willing to share with Xue Tian. \n\nPlease recover the treasure from Poseidon's Plunder so I can give it to Xue.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is that what you found? Impressive! Xue will be thrilled to see this! \n\nYou know, he’s afraid of the water. He puts on a brave face about it, but that’s why he won’t go out to the submerged shipwrecks.

Title: Treasured Company
Description: Bring a letter from Wafa Keles to Xue Tien
PlayerPrompt: "You could ask him to appraise it."
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Yes! I could say I found this goblet, and ask him to take a look. I like it! 

But I’m so nervous! Just the thought of talking to him makes me weak-kneed. 

Could you take him a message asking him to check it out?
InProgressResponse: I know I’ll have to talk to Xue on my own someday… but could you ask him to stop by for me? \n\nTell him about Poseidon’s Goblet and see if he is interested in a business partnership.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: A message from Wafa Keles asking me to appraise something called Poseidon’s Goblet? Sounds intriguing… \n\nBut I must ask – are they still standing out in the water?

Title: Not Another Fish in the Sea
Description: Recover Xue's Sea Glass Charms from the Treetop pirates that stole them.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I needed some space. And had to get away from my overbearing family. \n\nI came here to find peace of mind. Then I saw Wafa, and I knew I found what I'd been looking for.
InProgressResponse: Those Treetop pirates stole my Sea Glass Charms. \n\nThey would be a perfect gift for Wafa. Please get them back.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Those are perfect! \n\nCan you imagine them hanging from their hair, catching the sunlight as they dance through the waves?

Title: Meat For Nekumanesh (Expedition)
Description: Collect Hunks of Meat for Nekumanesh the alligator from Corrupted Leaders in The Depths Expedition.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: (The alligator snaps at you, clearly offended by the insinuation that he isn't big enough.)
InProgressResponse: (Nekumanesh looks at you suspiciously. He had been expecting you to return with food.)
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: (With a hearty snap of his jaws, Nekumanesh eats up all the meat you gave him like he'd been starving. Did he just get a little bigger…?)
